<p>Alongside being a two-time Mr. Olympia winner, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/francocolumbu" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Frank Columbu</a> was well-known as Arnold Schwarzenegger&#8217;s training partner. In 1976, he won his first Mr. Olympia title, with most putting this down to his deep, striated chest muscles.</p>



<p>After suffering an injury in 1977 while competing in the World&#8217;s Strongest Man, Frank won his second title in 1981. At 5′5″ and less than 200 pounds, he was one of the smaller bodybuilders on stage. However, he definitely had enough size on his frame to make him a worthy Mr. Olympia winner.</p>



