<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/thedorianyates" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Dorian Yates</a>, known as <em>The Shadow,</em> is regarded by many as the first bodybuilder to start the mass monster era. This marked the start of size over aesthetics, nudging fellow bodybuilders to pack on as much size as humanly possible.</p>



<p>Weighing over 30 pounds more than Arnold on stage, Dorian certainly redefined the meaning of huge. Because of this, he dominated the Olympia stage in the 1990s, winning six consecutive titles.</p>



<p>Alongside his size, he brought a new level of mass that’s still hard to find today. He pushed the boundaries of human physiology and we definitely do thank him for it!</p>



